    notes: "644KB PDF — Nevada Power (Southern NV) Q4 2025 commercial rate schedule. NV Energy is two utilities: Nevada Power (Southern, Las Vegas — primary DC market) and Sierra Pacific Power (Northern, Reno). LGS-3 = Large General Service tier 3; LGS-XP = Extra Power for transmission-voltage industrial. Las Vegas DC market is large (Switch, Google, Apple). NV Energy is non-ISO (WECC; participates in WEIM/EDAM). Capture LGS-3 + LGS-XP for SoNV as primary; SPP/SPC NoNV as supplementary. Extraction Caveats: The PDF contains multiple schedules. This record extracts Schedule LGS-3 (Large General Service-3) as it is the primary large-load schedule for customers with demand >= 1,000 kW. The 'fuel_adjustment_per_kwh' is set to the DEAA (Deferred Energy Accounting Adjustment) rate of $0.00594/kWh which is a standard component of the bundled rate. The 'energy_rate_peak_per_kwh' and 'energy_rate_off_peak_per_kwh' reflect the TOU (Time-of-Use) periods defined for LGS-3 (Summer on-peak: June 1-Sept 30, 3:01pm-9pm; Summer off-peak: All other hours; Winter: All hours). The 'off_peak_demand_charge_per_kw' is the Winter rate as LGS-3 does not specify a distinct Summer off-peak demand charge in the provided text snippet, implying the Winter rate applies or is the baseline. The 'min_load_mw' is set to 1.0 MW based on the eligibility criteria 'demand is 1,000 kW or greater'. The 'voltage_level' is 'Mixed' as LGS-3 covers both Primary and Secondary service rates depending on customer specifics, though the table lists both. The 'fuel_adjustment_clause' is true because the rate includes DEAA, TRED, REPR, EE, NDPP, and ESAP riders which are pass-through costs."
